<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>The Butterfly Encyclopedia</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary: #6c5ce7;
            --accent: #fd79a8;
            --dark: #2d3436;
            --light: #f9f9f9;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--light);
            margin: 0;
            color: var(--dark);
        }

        header {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary), var(--accent));
            color: white;
            padding: 3rem 1rem;
            text-align: center;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1100px;
            margin: 2rem auto;
            padding: 0 1rem;
        }

        .intro {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }

        /* Category Grid */
        .butterfly-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 2rem;
        }

        .card {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 15px;
            overflow: hidden;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }

        .card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-10px);
        }

        .card img {
            width: 100%;
            height: 200px;
            object-fit: cover;
        }

        .card-content {
            padding: 1.5rem;
        }

        .card-content h3 {
            margin-top: 0;
            color: var(--primary);
        }

        .tag {
            display: inline-block;
            background: #eee;
            padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 2rem;
            margin-top: 3rem;
            background: #eee;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>🦋 The Butterfly Encyclopedia</h1>
    <p>Exploring the vibrant world of Lepidoptera</p>
</header>

<div class="container">
    <section class="intro">
        <h2>Major Butterfly Families</h2>
        <p>There are roughly 17,500 species of butterflies in the world. They are generally grouped into six main families.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="butterfly-grid">
        <div class="card">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1551842323-66223e74390b?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=600" alt="Swallowtail">
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="tag">Papilionidae</span>
                <h3>Swallowtails</h3>
                <p>Recognizable by their "tails" on the hindwings. They are often large and brightly colored.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1543326105-06a9288f6920?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=600" alt="Monarch">
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="tag">Nymphalidae</span>
                <h3>Brush-footed Butterflies</h3>
                <p>The largest family, including Monarchs and Painted Ladies. They often walk on only four legs.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563294132-840974996963?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=600" alt="Sulphur Butterfly">
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="tag">Pieridae</span>
                <h3>Whites & Sulphurs</h3>
                <p>Mostly white, yellow, or orange. Common in gardens and known for mass migrations.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1594910360413-5a7a9cc5f67b?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=600" alt="Blue Butterfly">
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="tag">Lycaenidae</span>
                <h3>Gossamer-winged</h3>
                <p>Small butterflies including Blues, Coppers, and Hairstreaks. Known for their metallic shine.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1627318356942-df691238e55e?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=600" alt="Skipper Butterfly">
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="tag">Hesperiidae</span>
                <h3>Skippers</h3>
                <p>Small, fast-flying butterflies with hooked antennae and stout bodies.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1534438090956-2e9f6487532b?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=600" alt="Metalmark">
            <div class="card-content">
                <span class="tag">Riodinidae</span>
                <h3>Metalmarks</h3>
                <p>Named for the small metallic-looking spots typically found on their wings.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<footer>
    <p>&copy; 2026 Nature Explorers | Wings of the World</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
